{"type":"message","id":"f368b1f0","parentId":"6443d474","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:54:54.621Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 17:54 GMT+2] ENTERPRISE REPAIR & SHARED MEMORY UPGRADE.\n\n1.  **CI/CD Repair (`ci-cd.yml`):**\n    *   Set `python-version: \"3.12\"`.\n    *   Set `env.PYTHONPATH: ${{ github.workspace }}`.\n    *   Configure `gitleaks` with non-blocking warnings (if needed) or strict mode (preferred for Enterprise).\n\n2.  **Architecture v3.0 (`Shared Memory`):**\n    *   Create `src/core/shm_manager.py`.\n    *   *Logic:* Use `multiprocessing.shared_memory.ShareableList` to store `[CS2_Price, Rust_Price, TF2_Price, Dota_Price]`.\n    *   *Benefit:* Zero-copy read/write. No Redis serialization overhead.\n\n3.  **Visual Fix (`README.md`):**\n    *   Update Badge URLs to the exact provided string.\n    *   Add `Gitleaks | Protected` badge.\n\n4.  **Stress Test v3 (SHM):**\n    *   Run `src/stress_test_shm.py` (measure read/write latency).\n    *   *Target:* < 0.01ms.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   CI/CD Root Cause.\n    *   SHM Latency.\n    *   Commit Hash."}],"timestamp":1771170894619}}
{"type":"message","id":"dbd5a330","parentId":"f368b1f0","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:55:07.588Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Defining the Repair Scope**\n\nI'm currently focused on defining the initial scope. I've pinpointed the CI/CD configuration file, which seems like a good starting point. I'll need to identify the specific changes requested for the CI/CD pipeline, and ensure that everything is in order before proceeding.\n\n\n**Identifying the Configuration File**\n\nI'm zeroing in on the CI/CD configuration. I've located the likely file, `.github/workflows/ci-cd.yml`, and will next check the requested Python version update. Then, I'll tackle the `PYTHONPATH` environment variable modification.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771170902526_479","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter \"ci-cd.yml\""},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771170902672_480","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Filter \"README.md\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771170907245_481","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"src/stress_test_shm.py","content":"\nimport time\nimport multiprocessing\nfrom multiprocessing import shared_memory\nimport struct\n\ndef stress_test_shm():\n    # 4 floats (CS2, Rust, TF2, Dota) = 4 * 8 bytes (double) = 32 bytes\n    # actually ShareableList handles types, but for raw speed usually struct is better?\n    # The prompt asks for ShareableList explicitly: \"Use multiprocessing.shared_memory.ShareableList\"\n    \n    data = [0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0]\n    shm_name = \"stress_test_shm\"\n    \n    try:\n        sl = shared_memory.ShareableList(data, name=shm_name)\n    except FileExistsError:\n        # Cleanup if exists from previous run\n        existing = shared_memory.ShareableList(name=shm_name)\n        existing.shm.unlink()\n        sl = shared_memory.ShareableList(data, name=shm_name)\n\n    iterations = 100000\n    start_write = time.perf_counter()\n    for i in range(iterations):\n        sl[0] = float(i)\n        sl[1] = float(i)\n        sl[2] = float(i)\n        sl[3] = float(i)\n    end_write = time.perf_counter()\n    \n    start_read = time.perf_counter()\n    for i in range(iterations):\n        _ = sl[0]\n        _ = sl[1]\n        _ = sl[2]\n        _ = sl[3]\n    end_read = time.perf_counter()\n    \n    avg_write = ((end_write - start_write) / iterations) * 1000 # ms\n    avg_read = ((end_read - start_read) / iterations) * 1000 # ms\n    \n    print(f\"Write Latency: {avg_write:.5f} ms\")\n    print(f\"Read Latency: {avg_read:.5f} ms\")\n    \n    sl.shm.close()\n    sl.shm.unlink()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    stress_test_shm()\n"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771170907351_482","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\nfrom multiprocessing import shared_memory\nimport logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nclass SHMManager:\n    def __init__(self, name=\"prices_shm\", create=True):\n        self.name = name\n        # [CS2_Price, Rust_Price, TF2_Price, Dota_Price]\n        self.init_data = [0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0] \n        self.sl = None\n        if create:\n            self._create()\n        else:\n            self._attach()\n\n    def _create(self):\n        try:\n            self.sl = shared_memory.ShareableList(self.init_data, name=self.name)\n            logger.info(f\"SHM created: {self.name}\")\n        except FileExistsError:\n            logger.warning(f\"SHM {self.name} exists, attaching...\")\n            self._attach()\n\n    def _attach(self):\n        try:\n            self.sl = shared_memory.ShareableList(name=self.name)\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n             # Fallback if attach fails but should have created, or race condition\n             self.sl = shared_memory.ShareableList(self.init_data, name=self.name)\n\n    def update_prices(self, cs2=None, rust=None, tf2=None, dota=None):\n        if cs2 is not None: self.sl[0] = float(cs2)\n        if rust is not None: self.sl[1] = float(rust)\n        if tf2 is not None: self.sl[2] = float(tf2)\n        if dota is not None: self.sl[3] = float(dota)\n\n    def get_prices(self):\n        return {\n            \"CS2\": self.sl[0],\n            \"Rust\": self.sl[1],\n            \"TF2\": self.sl[2],\n            \"Dota\": self.sl[3]\n        }\n\n    def close(self):\n        if self.sl:\n            self.sl.shm.close()\n\n    def unlink(self):\n        if self.sl:\n            self.sl.shm.unlink()\n","file_path":"src/core/shm_manager.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771170907459_483","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":".github/workflows/ci-cd.yml"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771170907580_484","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"README.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4739,"output":1248,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5987,"cost":{"input":0.009478,"output":0.014976,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.024454}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771170894621}}
