{"type":"message","id":"31b2461e","parentId":"0cfdfe32","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:55:08.068Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771170907459_483","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"name: CI/CD Pipeline\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [ \"main\", \"dev\" ]\n\npermissions:\n  contents: read\n\njobs:\n  linting:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: \"3.12\"\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install flake8\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Lint with flake8\n        run: |\n          # stop the build if there are Python syntax errors or undefined names\n          flake8 . --count --select=E9,F63,F7,F82 --show-source --statistics\n          # exit-zero treats all errors as warnings. The GitHub editor is 127 chars wide\n          flake8 . --count --exit-zero --max-complexity=10 --max-line-length=127 --statistics\n\n  testing:\n    needs: linting\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.12\"]\n    env:\n      DRY_RUN: true\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install pytest\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Test with pytest\n        run: |\n          export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:.\n          pytest\n\n  security:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      actions: read\n      contents: read\n      security-events: write\n    strategy:\n      fail-fast: false\n      matrix:\n        language: [ 'python' ]\n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout repository\n        uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Initialize CodeQL\n        uses: github/codeql-action/init@v2\n        with:\n          languages: ${{ matrix.language }}\n      - name: Autobuild\n        uses: github/codeql-action/autobuild@v2\n      - name: Perform CodeQL Analysis\n        uses: github/codeql-action/analyze@v2\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771170908067}}
{"type":"message","id":"341610c7","parentId":"31b2461e","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:55:08.075Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771170907580_484","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 🤖 DMarket Telegram Bot (High-Frequency Trading Edition)\n\n[![CI](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/ci-cd.yml?branch=dev)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)](LICENSE)\n![Latency](https://img.shields.io/badge/Latency-30ms-brightgreen?logo=speedtest)\n![Skills](https://img.shields.io/badge/Skills-CS2%20%7C%20Dota2%20%7C%20Rust%20%7C%20TF2-orange)\n![Arch](https://img.shields.io/badge/Arch-Event--Driven-blueviolet)\n![Activity](https://img.shields.io/github/commit-activity/m/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)\n![Style](https://img.shields.io/badge/Code%20Style-Black-000000)\n\n> **Enterprise-grade automation** for DMarket interaction, featuring sub-millisecond latency and robust multiprocessing architecture powered by Gemini AI.\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Performance Dashboard\n\n| Metric | Standard Bot | MyClawDev (HFT) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Response Time** | `500ms` | **`0.03ms`** |\n| **Throughput** | `10 req/s` | **`1000+ req/s`** |\n| **Uptime** | `99.0%` | **`99.99%`** |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 AI Stack\n\nWe leverage a dual-model approach for optimal performance:\n\n*   **Gemini Pro 1.5**: Handles complex reasoning, market trend analysis, and strategic decision-making.\n*   **Gemini Flash**: Dedicated to ultra-low latency execution for arbitrage opportunities and sniping.\n\n---\n\n## 🏗️ Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Master[Master Controller] --> Redis[(Redis Message Broker)]\n    Redis --> CS2[CS2 Worker]\n    Redis --> Dota[Dota2 Worker]\n    Redis --> Rust[Rust Worker]\n    Redis --> TF2[TF2 Worker]\n    \n    style Master fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style Redis fill:#ff9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px\n    style CS2 fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style Dota fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style Rust fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n    style TF2 fill:#bbf,stroke:#333\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📜 Version History\n\n*   **v2.1:** Docker, GHCR, Enterprise CI/CD.\n*   **v2.0:** Multiprocessing, 40 Skills, 0.03ms Latency.\n*   **v1.0:** SACS-2026, Ed25519, Hot Reload.\n*   **v0.1:** Legacy script (Broken Async).\n\n## 🎮 Commands\n\n### General\n*   👋 `/start` - Initialize the bot interaction.\n*   ❓ `/help` - Show available commands.\n*   📊 `/status` - Check system health and uptime.\n*   ⚙️ `/settings` - Configure bot preferences.\n\n### Trading\n*   💰 `/balance` - View current DMarket balance.\n*   📦 `/inventory` - List items in inventory.\n*   📉 `/price <item>` - Check price for a specific item.\n*   🛒 `/buy <item>` - Initiate a buy order.\n*   🏷️ `/sell <item>` - Initiate a sell order.\n\n### Automation\n*   🤖 `/auto_buy` - Toggle auto-buy module.\n*   🔄 `/auto_sell` - Toggle auto-sell module.\n*   📜 `/history` - View transaction history.\n*   🛑 `/stop` - Emergency stop all active tasks.\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Deployment\n\n### Docker (Recommended)\n\n```bash\ndocker pull ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\ndocker run -d --env-file .env ghcr.io/dykij/dmarket-telegram-bot:latest\n```\n\n### Manual\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot.git\ncd DMarket-Telegram-Bot\npip install -r requirements.txt\npython main.py\n```\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771170908073}}
{"type":"message","id":"66665313","parentId":"341610c7","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:55:30.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Assessing the CI/CD Pipeline**\n\nI've examined the `ci-cd.yml` file, focusing on the Python versions and environment setup. Noticed the `linting` job uses a single string for `python-version`, while the `testing` job uses a matrix. The `PYTHONPATH` export also caught my attention.\n\n\n**Reviewing the CI/CD Changes**\n\nI've reviewed the proposed changes to the `ci-cd.yml` file. I've confirmed `python-version: [\"3.12\"]` in the testing matrix. I'm now implementing the `PYTHONPATH` modification, ensuring it's set in the `env` section as requested. Next, I'll integrate the `gitleaks` scanning step, opting for a new job for enhanced clarity.\n\n\n**Adjusting the Pipeline Configuration**\n\nI'm now focusing on the `ci-cd.yml` file, making precise modifications. I've successfully added the `PYTHONPATH` environment variable in the testing job. Currently, I'm working to integrate a `gitleaks` job, considering whether to incorporate it into an existing step or create a dedicated one. My approach involves a new `security-gitleaks` job with non-blocking warnings or, preferably, strict mode for thoroughness.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771170930621_485","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":".github/workflows/ci-cd.yml","oldText":"  testing:\n    needs: linting\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.12\"]\n    env:\n      DRY_RUN: true\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install pytest\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Test with pytest\n        run: |\n          export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:.\n          pytest","newText":"  testing:\n    needs: linting\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    strategy:\n      matrix:\n        python-version: [\"3.12\"]\n    env:\n      DRY_RUN: true\n      PYTHONPATH: ${{ github.workspace }}\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      - name: Set up Python ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n        uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n        with:\n          python-version: ${{ matrix.python-version }}\n      - name: Install dependencies\n        run: |\n          python -m pip install --upgrade pip\n          pip install pytest\n          if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then pip install -r requirements.txt; fi\n      - name: Test with pytest\n        run: |\n          pytest\n\n  gitleaks:\n    name: Gitleaks\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v3\n        with:\n          fetch-depth: 0\n      - uses: gitleaks/gitleaks-action@v2\n        env:\n          GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Configuring CI/CD Pipeline**\n\nI'm now implementing the CI/CD configuration. I've added the `PYTHONPATH` variable in the `testing` job. Next, I'm integrating the `gitleaks` step, opting for a new `security-gitleaks` job with `actions/checkout@v3` and `gitleaks/gitleaks-action@v2`. I'll next focus on updating `README.md`.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771170930856_486","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"# 🤖 DMarket Telegram Bot (High-Frequency Trading Edition)\n\n[![CI](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/ci-cd.yml?branch=dev)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)](LICENSE)\n![Gitleaks](https://img.shields.io/badge/Gitleaks-Protected-brightgreen)\n![Latency](https://img.shields.io/ba